Now, let us compute the standard deviation of the portfolio by determining the square root of the variance that we have computed in step 9. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Standard deviation}&= {\sqrt { 0.02345484}}\\
&= {\textbf{15.31\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The standard deviation of the portfolio is 15.31%.**
